  '<p>Locale resolution walks: explicit <code>?locale=</code> query → a <code>locale</code> cookie if the operator wires one → <code>Accept-Language</code> negotiation against <code>locales</code> → <code>defaultLocale</code>. The framework owns the negotiation, not the cookie wiring — operators set the cookie themselves via <code>res.cookie</code> on the route that switches locale.</p>',
  '<p>Filesystem loading: pass <code>{ dir: "./locales", lazyLoad: true, eagerLocales: ["en"] }</code> to keep boot fast — only the eager list loads at start; the rest load on first request and cache for the process lifetime. Inline <code>translations: {}</code> and <code>lazyLoad: true</code> are mutually exclusive.</p>',
